Phase 5.5 prerequisite for v2 promotion. The fork's production tree
had 1 high-severity advisory (picomatch ReDoS via extglob
quantifiers, transitively pulled via ignore@7.0.5 used in the gitignore
walker). npm audit fix --omit=dev bumps picomatch to a patched
version in package-lock.json. No package.json edits, no breaking
changes. Production-scope npm audit now reports 0 vulnerabilities.

See runs/feasibility_v2_analyzer/phase5_npm_audit.md in the consuming
project for the full review.
---
 package-lock.json | 6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/package-lock.json b/package-lock.json
index b1454f6..53a7388 100644
--- a/package-lock.json
+++ b/package-lock.json
@@ -1229,9 +1229,9 @@
